{"id": 223749914, "title": "Tiffani Thiessen is 'heartbroken' over death of her father: 'I loved making you proud'", "text": "Tiffani Thiessen is mourning the loss of her father, Frank Thiessen, who died at the age of 85. \u201cMy Dad was a lover of many things. Animals, plants, chocolate, jazz, anything citrus, lottery tickets, cars, watches, stray dogs & cats and good Italian pasta. But what he loved most was his family,\u201d the \u201cSaved by the Bell\u201d alum wrote in a lengthy tribute announcing the sad news via Instagram on May 24. \u201cHe was a quiet man, but was never quiet about showing his love for us. He was kind, had a sweet sense of humor and was the utmost gentleman. Everybody who knew my Dad LOVED him. He truly had a heart of gold.\u201d Tiffani\u2019s post included a carousel of photos of her dad over the years, featuring snaps of the father-daughter duo along with the actress\u2019 brother Todd. The emotional photo dump also included sweet pics of Frank being a doting grandfather to Tiffani\u2019s two children \u2013 Holt 8, and Harper, 13 \u2013 whom she shares with husband Brady Smith. The \u201cBeverly Hills, 90210\u201d alum, 50, went on to admit that she is \u201cheartbroken\u201d by her father\u2019s passing. \u201cHowever, I know you are at peace now and that brings me comfort. I promise you I will watch over Mom [Robyn Ernest] and take care of her as you did for over 60 years,\u201d she continued. \u201cThank you for being such a dedicated husband and showing me what a true gentleman is. Thank you for being a wonderful Dad and Gramps and being there for us.\u201d The actress concluded her post by thanking her dad for \u201cloving\u201d her like he always did. \u201cNo matter what, you had my back and were my biggest fan. I loved making you proud,\u201d she gushed. \u201cI love you, Daddy. We miss you so much.\u201d The sad news comes shortly after Frank celebrated his last birthday on Feb. 3. \u201cHappy 85th Birthday Daddy! Another year around the sun and another candle added to your cake. (? of course),\u201d Tiffani wrote via Instagram at the time. \u201cSo much to be proud and thankful for and you\u2019re one of them. I \u2764\ufe0f you Daddy!\u201d Plenty of Tiffani\u2019s famous pals have since flooded the comments sections of her posts with words of support and sympathy. \u201cGod Bless you and the family Tiff. Losing a parent is so incredibly hard. I can\u2019t imagine your pain and grief at this time\u2026 Love you honey, sending nothing but love,\u201d wrote Mario Lopez, with her former \u201c90210\u201d co-star Jason Priestley adding, \u201cSo sorry for you loss Tiff. Sending you love and light.\u201d", "summary": "\u201cThank you for loving me like you always did. No matter what, you had my back and were my biggest fan. I loved making you proud,\u201d the \u201cBeverly Hills, 90210\u201d alum wrote.", "url": "https://pagesix.com/2024/05/26/celebrity-news/tiffani-thiessen-heartbroken-over-death-of-her-father/", "image": "https://pagesix.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2024/05/Tiffani-Thiessen-death-of-her-father.jpg?quality=75&strip=all&w=1200", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 15:58:27", "author": "Nicki Gostin", "authors": ["Nicki Gostin"], "language": "en", "source_country": "us", "sentiment": 0.524}